---
description: Rules for refactoring python code
alwaysApply: false
---

- Use modern Python type hints: `list[str]` not `List[str]`, `dict[str, int]` not `Dict[str, int]`
- Simplify complex code: extract functions, split large classes, separate concerns into modules
- Clean up naming and docs: remove obvious comments, improve function names, keep docs concise
